1
00:00:06,220 --> 00:00:13,100
It's fun to watch gifts and talents being used in our midst. That's exciting. Welcome this morning.

2
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:18,000
This is the day the Lord has made. Amen? Amen. Amen.

3
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:24,760
Well, I'm excited about sharing this message today. I think it's very important.

4
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:28,500
I'm excited about the topic for the next few weeks. So hang on.

5
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:35,930
I think one of the biggest questions that we can ask about life is this.

6
00:00:35,930 --> 00:00:39,490
why in the world are we here?

7
00:00:40,470 --> 00:00:41,170
Why are we here?

8
00:00:41,950 --> 00:00:44,330
Why are you here?

9
00:00:45,350 --> 00:00:47,610
And we can answer this biblically.

10
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,910
We can say we are here to love God

11
00:00:50,910 --> 00:00:53,570
and to manage His creation.

12
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:55,640
To love God.

13
00:00:56,590 --> 00:00:57,790
To take care of the world

14
00:00:57,790 --> 00:01:02,430
on behalf of God as stewards unto the Lord.

15
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:05,380
How do I love God?

16
00:01:05,380 --> 00:01:07,770
And how do I manage the creation?

17
00:01:08,780 --> 00:01:16,820
We can answer by saying this, by following Jesus Christ as your Lord and Savior and to

18
00:01:16,820 --> 00:01:19,940
exercise your spiritual gifts.

19
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:31,510
And you can answer, I love Jesus, but what in the world are you talking about when it

20
00:01:31,510 --> 00:01:32,650
comes to spiritual gifts?

21
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,320
And that's where we're going.

22
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:40,000
Today and the next few weeks, what are spiritual gifts?

23
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:43,660
What are your spiritual gifts?

24
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:46,570
How do you use them?

25
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:48,570
What are they for?

26
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:53,300
What difference will they make in your life?

27
00:01:54,790 --> 00:02:00,050
Important, I believe, and compelling questions that we must answer.

28
00:02:00,050 --> 00:02:06,480
And we will seek to answer them and explore them for your joy and for God's glory.

29
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:09,670
So hang on, and here we go.

30
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:15,630
Number one, why focus on spiritual gifts?

31
00:02:16,350 --> 00:02:19,070
Why in the world would we even explore this?

32
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:25,090
The Bible says in 1 Corinthians 12, in verse 1, I share it with you.

33
00:02:25,090 --> 00:02:26,490
Paul writes,

34
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:35,560
Now concerning spiritual gifts, brothers and sisters, I do not want you to be uninformed.

35
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:37,400
Uninformed.

36
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:44,060
For some, ignorance is bliss, right?

37
00:02:44,660 --> 00:02:48,340
Some things you'd rather, I just don't want to know about that.

38
00:02:48,620 --> 00:02:49,680
I'll carry on.

39
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:50,800
I don't want to know.

40
00:02:51,770 --> 00:02:56,110
And that may be a way to live life for some, and it works in certain circumstances.

41
00:02:56,110 --> 00:03:01,310
But I don't think in this area that's a path we should follow.

42
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:08,740
Spiritual gifts is not a place for us to tune out and to be ignorant of.

43
00:03:09,670 --> 00:03:10,410
Three reasons.

44
00:03:10,530 --> 00:03:15,190
One, when we ignore spiritual gifts, when we become ignorant of spiritual gifts,

45
00:03:15,830 --> 00:03:21,690
friends, we miss out on joy and blessing in using those gifts.

46
00:03:22,010 --> 00:03:24,650
We miss out on joy.

47
00:03:24,650 --> 00:03:29,230
We miss out on blessing from the Lord as we use them.

48
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:40,590
I'll submit that we'll find meaning and purpose and joy in serving the Lord as we use spiritual gifts.

49
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:48,890
I have found that people that know what their gifts are, that are using them on a regular basis,

50
00:03:49,290 --> 00:03:52,950
they generally have a sense of God's calling in their life.

51
00:03:53,190 --> 00:03:55,230
They have a healthy sense of self-esteem.

52
00:03:55,990 --> 00:03:59,850
They know what they're doing, where they're going, and why.

53
00:04:01,170 --> 00:04:02,310
What a blessing that is.

54
00:04:03,860 --> 00:04:06,120
They know where they fit in God's kingdom.

55
00:04:07,450 --> 00:04:11,190
And I would submit again, that's an exciting place for us to be.

56
00:04:13,410 --> 00:04:13,970
That's number one.

57
00:04:14,050 --> 00:04:16,830
Two, you miss out if you're ignorant of spiritual gifts.

58
00:04:16,830 --> 00:04:23,370
You miss out on being part of meaningfully building the church and growing the kingdom of God.

59
00:04:23,990 --> 00:04:29,070
You miss out on being part of something holy and larger than yourself.

60
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:31,770
Oh, how fun that is.

61
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:37,380
I think also, number three, by ignoring our spiritual gifts.

62
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:39,240
This is important.

63
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:45,540
I think we are holding back God's means for effectiveness in the church today.

64
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:53,420
If God has called us as a mission, with a mission in the world to grow the church,

65
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,880
we must be effective in doing so.

66
00:04:55,880 --> 00:05:03,960
I believe that God makes the church effective by gifting it with certain gifts to make it grow and be effective.

67
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:10,380
John MacArthur, a pastor in the valley next door, said this.

68
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:20,100
He says, no local congregation will be what it should be, what Jesus prayed that it would be,

69
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:24,140
what the Holy Spirit gifted it and empowered it to be

70
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:29,360
until the church understands spiritual gifts.

71
00:05:30,670 --> 00:05:31,970
Strong statement.

72
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:36,320
True, I think, to the core.

73
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:42,440
To continue building this case to help us understand

74
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:45,280
why in the world we must explore spiritual gifts,

75
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,960
I want to share a portion of a video

76
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:51,460
of a gentleman that has blessed my life in many ways.

77
00:05:51,460 --> 00:06:00,360
You're about to see Bill Hybels, the pastor of the largest church in America, started in a movie theater over 20 years ago.

78
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:09,680
And you're going to see him as he was speaking to the delegates of the American Baptist churches at our national convention in 1997.

79
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:12,460
It's a short clip.

80
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:16,920
The sound, of course, is him speaking to a hall of 5,000 people.

81
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:21,600
So it's not as clear as I'd like it to be,

82
00:06:21,940 --> 00:06:25,280
but please listen to the message underneath.

83
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,980
So important and very powerful.

84
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:28,740
Bill Hybels.

85
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:47,600
A community of servants, men and women,

86
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,360
stewarding their spiritual gifts.

87
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,460
And every part of that is important.

88
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:56,620
We wanted to be a unified community of servants.

89
00:06:58,450 --> 00:07:01,470
Today is an era of consumerism.

90
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:03,310
Christians move into a community.

91
00:07:03,310 --> 00:07:04,990
They do some church shopping.

92
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:08,010
They rate the church by the preaching, by the music, by the youth.

93
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:11,390
They move in, sit down, and consume ministry.

94
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:14,880
Nothing is further from the heart of Christ.

95
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,840
The Apostle Paul used to start his letters by saying,

96
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:21,340
I, Paul, a servant of Jesus Christ.

97
00:07:21,420 --> 00:07:23,760
This is fundamental to my identity.

98
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,140
My name is Paul.

99
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:29,940
My identity is that of a bondservant of Jesus Christ,

100
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,960
committed to the local church.

101
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,080
And we've said all the days of Willow Creek,

102
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:37,780
When you join the family of God here, you put the towel over your arm.

103
00:07:38,890 --> 00:07:41,690
And the issue is not whether or not you're going to serve.

104
00:07:41,770 --> 00:07:42,690
It's just where.

105
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:46,010
And then we teach people about spiritual gifts.

106
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:48,530
And you know what we actually discovered?

107
00:07:48,730 --> 00:07:51,650
I mean, I may not say much of value tonight,

108
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:55,210
but what I'm going to say these next few moments is really deep.

109
00:07:56,690 --> 00:07:58,130
Trust me, it's deep.

110
00:07:59,610 --> 00:08:02,750
When we studied all about spiritual gifts, it dawned on us one day,

111
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:14,650
what do you mean it was in the mind of god for the church to be led by people with leadership

112
00:08:14,650 --> 00:08:19,590
gifts and taught by people with teaching gifts and administrated by people with administration

113
00:08:19,590 --> 00:08:30,840
gifts and shepherded by people with shepherding gifts that blew our minds it's what the scriptures

114
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:38,210
teach god's given me opportunity to teach all over the world teach church leaders all over

115
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:41,970
the world. And friends, I don't say this. I mean, I just say it to our embarrassment.

116
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:49,590
My unofficial estimate, there is not one percent of evangelical churches worldwide

117
00:08:49,590 --> 00:08:59,500
that are organized according to spiritual gifts. I don't get it. When churches are not led by

118
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:04,980
people with leadership gifts, there's trouble in the church. When churches aren't taught by

119
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:10,160
people with teaching gifts, that's trouble in the church. When the church is not administrated by

120
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:15,430
people with administration gifts, shepherded by people with shepherding. Boy, I'll tell you,

121
00:09:15,470 --> 00:09:22,330
we caught on to that and we said, we can't mess much with other churches, but as for our church,

122
00:09:22,690 --> 00:09:32,180
we're going to be a unified community of servants, men and women, stewarding their

123
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:42,800
spiritual gifts to the glory of God and the common good of the church. Did you catch how powerful

124
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:52,870
That principle is men and women stewarding their gifts that God has given for the glory of God and to grow the church.

125
00:09:54,390 --> 00:10:00,930
And what really amazes me about that statement was, as Bill has taught around the world, he says, let me just say it again,

126
00:10:00,930 --> 00:10:07,090
less than 1% of the churches, evangelical churches around the world, are organized by spiritual gifts.

127
00:10:07,990 --> 00:10:10,950
People leading churches without leadership gifts.

128
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:13,770
People teaching who don't have teaching gifts.

129
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:18,250
And no wonder the church is in conflict, upside down, doing crazy things.

130
00:10:22,650 --> 00:10:23,550
It's a powerful statement.

131
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:26,250
When they started that church, they began to say,

132
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:32,170
people with the various gifts will be organized that way that the gifts operate and are effective.

133
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:35,120
God's kingdom might grow.

134
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:38,300
Rick Warren has said this.

135
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:41,720
A local pastor of one of the other largest churches in America said this.

136
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:48,860
He said, for the church to grow, the pastor must give up the ministry.

137
00:10:50,170 --> 00:10:53,730
And the people must give up the leadership.

138
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:57,880
That's also huge.

139
00:10:59,650 --> 00:11:03,130
Pastors have to stop doing ministry, and the people have to stop leading.

140
00:11:04,110 --> 00:11:05,510
It's got to be flipped around.

141
00:11:05,870 --> 00:11:07,950
Let pastors who are gifted to lead, lead,

142
00:11:08,090 --> 00:11:11,130
and let the people who are gifted for ministry do the ministry.

143
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:13,210
Then it spreads and it grows.

144
00:11:14,070 --> 00:11:17,410
Otherwise, you continue to have churches of 75 people.

145
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:21,660
Friends, that's the average-sized church in America.

146
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:22,620
Did you know that?

147
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:26,790
75. When I go back east and I meet

148
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:30,810
with conferees and delegates and they find out we've got 400

149
00:11:30,810 --> 00:11:35,540
people, they think we're a mega church. Because when they've

150
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:39,600
got 40 people in the pew every week, they think we are just

151
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:43,670
the cat's meow. And I think we're great. But we can be

152
00:11:43,670 --> 00:11:49,210
a lot better. We're good, but we can be better. And my

153
00:11:49,210 --> 00:11:54,460
sights are on a whole different plane. I don't want to grow from 400

154
00:11:54,460 --> 00:11:58,620
to 420. I want to see spiritual gifts liberated

155
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:02,700
that this place explodes because people are finding

156
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:06,600
Christ throughout this community and getting whole in their spirit

157
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:10,500
and their bodies and their psyches and everything because people are gifted to do

158
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:19,130
ministry from this place. Small churches

159
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:23,270
become bigger ones if the pastor does the leading and the people will do the

160
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:26,730
ministry. You know, we've talked about that for years.

161
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:30,460
My first sermon I preached here was Ephesians chapter 4,

162
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:31,900
and I laid this principle out.

163
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:36,560
But it's hard to go from talking about it to living it out.

164
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:40,890
Because to live it out, you have to change how we think about

165
00:12:40,890 --> 00:12:44,530
how we all interact with each other and how we interact with this place.

166
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:48,510
And now we're beginning to really look at these issues on a deep level.

167
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:50,450
Friends, I'm going to ask this question.

168
00:12:50,850 --> 00:12:53,830
Are you ready to do the ministry?

169
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,500
Are you ready to be trained?

170
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,360
to do the ministry?

171
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:04,120
Are you ready to let God use you

172
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,280
in building up the kingdom of God?

173
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,500
It's not just the pastors that do the building

174
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:16,160
because we only can reach so deep and so far and so wide.

175
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:21,060
Are you ready to build God's kingdom

176
00:13:21,060 --> 00:13:22,840
as he empowers you?

177
00:13:23,830 --> 00:13:27,530
And as we pastors train you, are you ready?

178
00:13:27,530 --> 00:13:32,480
We find joy in finding our spiritual gifts.

179
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:35,740
We see an effectiveness in the church rise.

180
00:13:37,350 --> 00:13:39,970
That's why we focus on spiritual gifts.

181
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:44,030
Number two, let's define what they are.

182
00:13:44,710 --> 00:13:46,610
What are spiritual gifts anyway?

183
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:55,500
They're special abilities given by God to his followers for the development of the church.

184
00:13:56,960 --> 00:14:01,060
Some verses from Scripture, I think, will lay this out and build the case.

185
00:14:01,060 --> 00:14:04,620
Romans chapter 12, Paul says this, verse 3,

186
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:10,730
As God's messenger, I give each of you this warning.

187
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:15,060
Be honest in your estimate of yourselves,

188
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:20,800
measuring your value by how much faith God has given you.

189
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:31,060
Just as our bodies have many parts and each part has a special function, so it is with Christ's body.

190
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:37,110
We are all parts of his one body and each of us has different work to do.

191
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:45,110
And since we are all one body in Christ, we belong to each other and each of us needs all the others.

192
00:14:45,670 --> 00:14:51,720
God has given each of us the ability to do certain things well.

193
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:55,660
Friends, please hear this.

194
00:14:56,100 --> 00:15:00,800
God has given each of you something, if not many things,

195
00:15:01,060 --> 00:15:03,660
he wants you to do well in the kingdom.

196
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:07,180
Amen.

197
00:15:09,270 --> 00:15:10,510
1 Peter 4.10

198
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:15,380
God has given gifts to each of you

199
00:15:15,380 --> 00:15:18,900
from his great variety of spiritual gifts.

200
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,480
Now manage them well

201
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:26,120
so that God's generosity can flow through you.

202
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,280
Manage them well.

203
00:15:29,210 --> 00:15:29,970
Use them.

204
00:15:30,290 --> 00:15:31,730
Train yourself in them.

205
00:15:32,610 --> 00:15:33,850
Experiment with them.

206
00:15:34,130 --> 00:15:35,190
Grow with them.

207
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:36,850
But use them.

208
00:15:37,690 --> 00:15:38,570
Manage them well.

209
00:15:41,780 --> 00:15:44,240
For those who like to take notes, I've given you this definition.

210
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,180
You can take this down.

211
00:15:45,180 --> 00:15:58,560
A spiritual gift is a special ability that God gives according to his grace to each member of the body of Christ

212
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:02,740
to be used for the development of the church.

213
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:08,090
That's what spiritual gifts are all about.

214
00:16:10,330 --> 00:16:15,790
Before we go too far, I'd like for us also to hear what they're not.

215
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:21,430
Because there are other things we can confuse to be spiritual gifts.

216
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:26,190
Spiritual gifts are not natural talents.

217
00:16:27,630 --> 00:16:29,130
They are not natural talents.

218
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:36,400
Everyone, whether you are a Christian or not, you have certain talents, certain natural

219
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:39,180
abilities that you simply have.

220
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,580
They give us self-identity.

221
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:42,960
They're usually physical.

222
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,340
They're something you can do well.

223
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:48,400
Spiritual gifts are not the same as natural talents.

224
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:56,010
Spiritual gifts are also not the same thing as the fruit of the Spirit.

225
00:16:57,090 --> 00:17:00,250
Galatians chapter 5 lays out the fruit of the Spirit.

226
00:17:00,670 --> 00:17:03,590
Love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, and so forth.

227
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:06,070
Those are not spiritual gifts.

228
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:13,070
Those are fruit of the Spirit that are to be exercised, to be lived out in every believer's life.

229
00:17:13,390 --> 00:17:22,400
As we mature in Christ, our lives should be filled more and more with love and joy and peace and patience and kindness.

230
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:24,180
And that's for all of us.

231
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:29,270
Spiritual gifts are different than the fruit of the Spirit.

232
00:17:32,010 --> 00:17:37,370
The spiritual gifts are also not Christian roles that we might play.

233
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:43,880
Roles are mannerisms in which we participate as Christians.

234
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:47,920
We are all to be people of faith.

235
00:17:48,560 --> 00:17:54,000
We are all to be people of prayer, of hospitality, of witness, and things like that.

236
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:58,360
These we just do in the natural course of following Jesus.

237
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:01,080
Certain roles that we play.

238
00:18:01,460 --> 00:18:04,400
Spiritual gifts are not those roles.

239
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:14,690
And spiritual gifts, finally, are not what I'm going to just say are counterfeit gifts that we see in the world today.

240
00:18:14,690 --> 00:18:26,680
There are people out there that can interpret omens, that channel spirits, that have extrasensory

241
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:32,180
perception, that talk with the dead on television, and all kinds of things like that.

242
00:18:33,850 --> 00:18:37,950
Those are not spiritual gifts, as God defines from His Word.

243
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:45,040
Those are spiritual realities, and the Bible is very clear we are not to participate in

244
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:45,620
those realms.

245
00:18:45,620 --> 00:18:51,080
You open yourself to very negative, demonic, spiritual oppression when you go there.

246
00:18:52,590 --> 00:18:56,370
Those are not spiritual gifts as we are looking at here.

247
00:18:56,650 --> 00:18:58,390
I'm not saying those are not real.

248
00:18:59,620 --> 00:19:03,300
I'm saying they're not for followers of Jesus to participate in.

249
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:09,700
And friends, if you have opened your life to some of those issues, we need to pray and talk about that.

250
00:19:10,660 --> 00:19:16,020
I don't mean to be hairy scary, but I want to say there are big spiritual issues in the world.

251
00:19:16,020 --> 00:19:22,080
And when we dabble, we open ourselves to forces and spiritual realities that are not of God.

252
00:19:27,340 --> 00:19:29,080
We know what spiritual gifts are now.

253
00:19:29,890 --> 00:19:32,490
And we know, in a sense, what they are not.

254
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:41,140
So the question arises, okay, do I have one gift or more than one?

255
00:19:43,580 --> 00:19:48,690
Each of us has at least one and probably more.

256
00:19:48,690 --> 00:19:55,300
In the literature and the study of spiritual gifts, we talk about them as a gift mix.

257
00:19:56,680 --> 00:20:01,280
Because certain gifts do tend to couple with other gifts.

258
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:06,420
And personality types play into this as well.

259
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:12,680
But spiritual gifts often come hooked together two or three at a time to make a package of ministry.

260
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:22,700
As I've been studying spiritual gifts and taking inventories and experimenting and talking with others and getting their wisdom,

261
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:34,380
I seem, this is just for me, I seem to have gifts in the area of teaching and wisdom, knowledge, leadership, and apostleship.

262
00:20:35,980 --> 00:20:43,200
And I'm also testing out whether underneath I may have shepherding, discernment, and evangelism.

263
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:45,240
But those seem to be second tier.

264
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:52,180
Different gift mixes create different combinations of the kinds of ministry that are possible

265
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:58,780
and can be experienced with joy and effectiveness as God blesses each of you.

266
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:04,870
I hope I'm making you excited to discover how has God gifted me.

267
00:21:06,380 --> 00:21:08,240
What a great joy it is to figure that out.

268
00:21:10,340 --> 00:21:16,000
And so this morning, I'd like to begin in a three-part series.

269
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:19,820
and the 4th, on October 6th, you'll have an opportunity

270
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:24,120
to truly try and delve in and find out what your spiritual gifts

271
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:28,100
are all about. You will not want to miss any of this series, but you

272
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:32,190
must be here October 6th. Do you hear what I'm saying? You must

273
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:36,570
be here October 6th. Baseball games, football

274
00:21:36,570 --> 00:21:40,470
games, doesn't matter, vacations, you must be here October

275
00:21:40,470 --> 00:21:46,840
6th. We got it? Okay. Let's talk about

276
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:50,240
what we have termed as our the red gifts.

277
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:52,780
Why red?

278
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:58,520
Red is a color that reminds us

279
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:02,360
of what Jesus Christ did on the cross.

280
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:07,860
It can be thought of as a symbol of commitment to Jesus.

281
00:22:08,540 --> 00:22:13,520
After all, it was Jesus' blood that flowed for us from the cross.

282
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:19,260
Red deeply connects with Jesus and his mission in the world.

283
00:22:20,670 --> 00:22:28,230
And so we term the red gifts as gifts that help us proclaim the message of Jesus Christ

284
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:32,610
and help people grow in their knowledge of Jesus.

285
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:36,080
So we call them the red gifts.

286
00:22:37,550 --> 00:22:40,190
And I'm going to share a list of these gifts.

287
00:22:40,190 --> 00:22:45,530
I encourage you to just jot them down and perhaps flesh out these definitions

288
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:50,970
and begin to think, is the Lord using you perhaps in some of these areas?

289
00:22:51,590 --> 00:23:01,040
And when? October 6th, you'll get to be here to really find out at a deeper level how God is gifting you.

290
00:23:02,670 --> 00:23:09,450
The red gifts begin, and I've just listed the first one this way, evangelism.

291
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:22,510
evangelism evangelism those with the gift of evangelism are enabled to communicate the gospel

292
00:23:22,510 --> 00:23:29,330
to non-christians to pre-christians in a manner that is conducive for them to come to faith

293
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:40,080
billy graham bless that man's heart you know what as a preacher sometimes i get really frustrated

294
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:47,770
with Billy Graham. Because I could have said that, and yet thousands come to find Jesus.

295
00:23:48,730 --> 00:23:56,560
He doesn't say anything new or radical, but he is gifted by God. I sound like Salieri sometimes,

296
00:23:56,560 --> 00:24:01,640
and he's Mozart, and it drives me crazy. I could have said that, but I wasn't gifted

297
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:10,420
to say it with his power and his persona and God's spirit on his life. It's a spiritual gift.

298
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,800
It's amazing to watch.

299
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:14,780
Amazing to watch.

300
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:24,040
There are some people that can get in a conversation with somebody else in the most natural way,

301
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:28,560
and the next thing you know, they are pouring out their life to Christ.

302
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:30,160
It's amazing.

303
00:24:30,660 --> 00:24:37,310
Now, that doesn't say that because they're gifted, that takes the responsibility off of us.

304
00:24:37,770 --> 00:24:39,350
We're all to be witnesses.

305
00:24:39,610 --> 00:24:41,410
That's a role that we play.

306
00:24:41,410 --> 00:24:51,490
But there are people who are specially gifted in being able to connect and share and talk and people come to Christ just like that.

307
00:24:52,760 --> 00:25:01,350
Research shows that about 10% of any given congregation has this gift.

308
00:25:03,180 --> 00:25:09,540
And as I may have shared before, I'm bothered by that because we've got to figure out who you are.

309
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:16,130
because you need to stop whatever else you're doing and use that gift.

310
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:21,370
And we joke around here talking about councils and boards and stuff.

311
00:25:21,370 --> 00:25:28,120
We've got to fire you from everything you're doing and get you out there using your gift.

312
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:35,830
That's when the church gets effective, when you're gifted using your gift.

313
00:25:38,630 --> 00:25:43,540
People with evangelism gifts are good at preaching.

314
00:25:43,540 --> 00:25:56,590
They're good at visitation ministry and missions, church planting, outreach community, outreach ministries to the community, to children, to internationals, you name it.

315
00:25:56,730 --> 00:26:04,010
It doesn't matter who, but they're good at communicating the message to people, and people come to Christ.

316
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:09,390
Ten percent of you have this gift, and many of you perhaps don't even know it.

317
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:12,720
We must find out who you are.

318
00:26:13,380 --> 00:26:15,880
You must find out who you are.

319
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:19,880
It's my mission to find out who you are.

320
00:26:21,590 --> 00:26:22,230
Evangelism.

321
00:26:22,650 --> 00:26:25,130
Others are gifted in the area of missions.

322
00:26:27,910 --> 00:26:30,750
It's different than the first one we talked about

323
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:35,630
because missionaries, by definition, take it to a second culture.

324
00:26:36,410 --> 00:26:43,390
They have a special ability given by God to work in and adapt to a second culture.

325
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,820
They love to be overseas.

326
00:26:47,380 --> 00:26:50,540
They don't feel right being in their own culture.

327
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:58,980
They must, by God's design, be somewhere else in a different culture working and planting churches and doing ministry.

328
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:06,180
Now that also might mean, though, simply working across town in a different culture here in the United States.

329
00:27:08,620 --> 00:27:15,000
You don't have to fly around the world, but your heartbeat, if you have this gift of missionary and missions,

330
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:19,380
is you must be in a second culture, a different culture,

331
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:23,620
working amongst those people in building up the church.

332
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:27,160
Some of you have this gift.

333
00:27:31,110 --> 00:27:39,060
The gift of apostle means that you are recognized by churches

334
00:27:39,060 --> 00:27:46,390
and a variety of churches in having responsibility and spiritual oversight in those churches

335
00:27:46,390 --> 00:27:50,130
and strategically planning the growth of those churches.

336
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:54,160
This is beyond the local level of the church here.

337
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:56,540
It's that farsighted perspective.

338
00:27:57,840 --> 00:28:03,840
I believe Dale Salico, our executive minister of our region and member of this church,

339
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:06,320
I believe he has this gift of apostleship.

340
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:10,100
He is a man with vision and abilities to grow the churches

341
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:18,420
and empower them with whatever is needed to grow this region of churches as an apostle.

342
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:25,860
They often work in denominational and larger perspectives.

343
00:28:29,690 --> 00:28:30,230
Counseling.

344
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:43,580
This gift enables Christians to serve others through comfort and encouragement and admonition.

345
00:28:45,390 --> 00:28:45,630
Why?

346
00:28:45,850 --> 00:28:49,670
So they can experience help and healing and comfort.

347
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:52,840
But it's for a short time.

348
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:54,860
For a short time.

349
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:56,880
Short-term perspective.

350
00:28:59,100 --> 00:29:04,760
Research also says that about 40% of those who have this gift also have the gift of hospitality.

351
00:29:05,520 --> 00:29:08,320
And you can see how those two come together very well.

352
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:16,080
Folks who have the gift of counseling need to be in hospital ministry, counseling team,

353
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:20,180
to be a gift counselor, helping others discern their spiritual gifts.

354
00:29:21,380 --> 00:29:27,800
They should be on prayer teams and in family counseling, ministering to various age groups

355
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:30,720
and prison ministries and things like that.

356
00:29:32,270 --> 00:29:33,970
Some of you have the gift of counseling,

357
00:29:35,150 --> 00:29:36,910
and we need to empower you and develop you

358
00:29:36,910 --> 00:29:40,370
and send you out for being more effective in that gift.

359
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:46,800
The next gift in the red category is leadership.

360
00:29:49,390 --> 00:29:52,550
It enables Christians to set goals for the church

361
00:29:52,550 --> 00:29:57,270
and to communicate them in a way that others get on board

362
00:29:57,270 --> 00:30:01,110
and jump in and want to be about what that church is doing.

363
00:30:02,390 --> 00:30:05,950
People naturally follow the leader, and if you've got leadership gifts,

364
00:30:06,350 --> 00:30:08,830
people are following you as you help build the church.

365
00:30:09,530 --> 00:30:12,370
Pastors, elders, worship leaders, department leaders,

366
00:30:12,370 --> 00:30:18,710
long-term planning strategists for the church should have the gift of leadership.

367
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:24,660
I contend that pastors today without leadership are in trouble.

368
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:32,300
Churches without good leaders with the gift of leadership are in trouble today.

369
00:30:35,120 --> 00:30:35,540
Shepherding.

370
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:46,160
Shepherding is a gift that enables a Christian to assume a long-term personal responsibility

371
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:49,660
for the spiritual well-being of a group of people.

372
00:30:51,630 --> 00:30:53,250
It can happen at a church level.

373
00:30:53,950 --> 00:30:56,210
It can happen even at a small group level.

374
00:30:57,650 --> 00:31:02,290
They're the ones that are committed over the long haul to see that this group of people

375
00:31:02,290 --> 00:31:07,010
grow and are healed and develop and mature and are nurtured.

376
00:31:10,190 --> 00:31:13,090
Pastors can have this gift, not always.

377
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:18,660
Not all pastors even have the gift of shepherding, and that's okay.

378
00:31:19,180 --> 00:31:22,000
They have others on the staff that have the gift of shepherding

379
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:27,320
because they may have a different gift of leadership and apostleship and other things.

380
00:31:29,490 --> 00:31:37,100
As Bill mentioned in the video, the shepherds need to be found and released to care for people

381
00:31:37,100 --> 00:31:40,380
and encourage them and build them up over the long term.

382
00:31:42,740 --> 00:31:43,260
Shepherds.

383
00:31:44,150 --> 00:31:57,400
Shepherds are involved in children's church, small group leaders, youth ministry, assimilation ministries, getting people plugged into this place, training programs and so forth and so on.

384
00:31:58,130 --> 00:31:59,190
It's the gift of shepherding.

385
00:31:59,510 --> 00:32:06,510
Some of you have this gift and you haven't even begun to use it.

386
00:32:07,070 --> 00:32:10,190
It's my goal that you discover it and develop it.

387
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:12,660
The gift of teaching.

388
00:32:15,510 --> 00:32:21,930
The gift of teaching allows that a Christian communicates the truth of the Scriptures

389
00:32:21,930 --> 00:32:28,350
in such a manner that others learn and it contributes to the health of the church.

390
00:32:30,620 --> 00:32:31,260
Give you an example.

391
00:32:32,530 --> 00:32:36,400
My wife is a teacher, a professional teacher.

392
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:42,710
And she is phenomenal in a classroom with children of a variety of ages.

393
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:52,100
But she and I both agree, she doesn't necessarily have the gift of teaching when it comes to adults,

394
00:32:52,420 --> 00:32:54,660
when it comes to biblical spiritual things.

395
00:32:56,290 --> 00:32:57,010
It's not her gift.

396
00:32:57,310 --> 00:32:59,010
She doesn't want to do that.

397
00:32:59,530 --> 00:33:00,850
It doesn't burn in her soul.

398
00:33:00,850 --> 00:33:03,910
And when she does try, it's okay.

399
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:11,200
Whereas others just naturally can speak from the scriptures and teach,

400
00:33:11,460 --> 00:33:14,720
and people's hearts are electrified and their lives change.

401
00:33:17,980 --> 00:33:19,520
I think I have that gift.

402
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:21,360
My wife does not.

403
00:33:21,580 --> 00:33:25,400
But I would never go in a classroom with 24 kids staring at me.

404
00:33:27,260 --> 00:33:28,060
No way.

405
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:32,460
And she would die a thousand deaths standing here staring at you.

406
00:33:33,450 --> 00:33:34,970
So it works out well this way.

407
00:33:36,980 --> 00:33:41,580
Teachers who have the spiritual gift of teaching must teach in the church.

408
00:33:41,580 --> 00:33:44,520
And those who don't have the gift of teaching should not teach

409
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:49,420
because God is not empowering them to teach spiritual things that life change happens.

410
00:33:53,820 --> 00:33:54,620
The gift of helps.

411
00:33:54,620 --> 00:34:10,340
The gift of helps is whereby God empowers Christians to place their own gifts at the disposal of other Christians,

412
00:34:12,140 --> 00:34:17,320
thus allowing that other Christian to use their gift more effectively.

413
00:34:18,290 --> 00:34:23,290
People with the gift of helps tend to focus on an individual

414
00:34:23,290 --> 00:34:28,450
and allow somebody, that person they're focusing on,

415
00:34:28,670 --> 00:34:31,070
to do their gift even more effectively.

416
00:34:34,430 --> 00:34:35,750
I think about, just off the cuff,

417
00:34:35,850 --> 00:34:40,380
John Maxwell has a man who is his prayer partner

418
00:34:40,380 --> 00:34:43,590
that follows John Maxwell,

419
00:34:43,810 --> 00:34:46,170
great pastor, teacher, leader, all over the nation.

420
00:34:46,170 --> 00:34:49,090
He follows him and he sits in the front row

421
00:34:49,090 --> 00:34:52,450
of every performance and he prays,

422
00:34:52,530 --> 00:34:54,850
interceding for John.

423
00:34:56,620 --> 00:34:58,620
He has prayer gifts, I believe,

424
00:34:58,620 --> 00:35:03,760
but he has the gift of helps that he might empower John to be more effective.

425
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:10,480
It's an amazing synergy as these two men work together for the kingdom of God.

426
00:35:12,790 --> 00:35:14,550
When I was a college pastor years ago,

427
00:35:16,090 --> 00:35:20,860
there was a young man in the church that was gifted in a lot of areas,

428
00:35:20,980 --> 00:35:24,780
in administration and phone calls and computers and things,

429
00:35:25,020 --> 00:35:27,840
and I was really out of touch with some of that stuff.

430
00:35:28,450 --> 00:35:31,630
And he just came every day for a couple hours

431
00:35:31,630 --> 00:35:36,990
and served me and freed me up to do other things that I was gifted for.

432
00:35:36,990 --> 00:35:43,530
And he loved being in the background to help me lead and teach

433
00:35:43,530 --> 00:35:47,460
and took over other things that I struggled with.

434
00:35:47,980 --> 00:35:54,780
And he wanted no recognition, no kudos, no public acknowledgement of any kind.

435
00:35:55,780 --> 00:36:00,490
I believe he had the gift of helps, for he truly helped me

436
00:36:00,490 --> 00:36:04,020
and we built the kingdom more effectively because of it.

437
00:36:06,500 --> 00:36:10,880
Similar to the gift of helps is the gift of service.

438
00:36:12,660 --> 00:36:14,860
This is one that's similar to helps,

439
00:36:14,860 --> 00:36:21,240
however, it enables the person to take their talents and gifts

440
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:24,120
and apply them to a body of believers,

441
00:36:24,860 --> 00:36:27,540
to an organization, towards a group.

442
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:32,560
These people have an eye to what needs to be done,

443
00:36:33,660 --> 00:36:34,660
and they do it.

444
00:36:36,190 --> 00:36:40,770
In the background, no public kudos, nothing like that.

445
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:45,290
They simply move in and do what needs to be done.

446
00:36:46,820 --> 00:36:51,580
And the church desperately needs these people as the backbone for what happens.

447
00:36:52,620 --> 00:36:53,660
And they do what needs to be done.

448
00:36:55,210 --> 00:36:59,550
Many of our gentlemen in our technical ministry have the gift of service.

449
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:05,120
Ken Lee has the gift of service.

450
00:37:06,510 --> 00:37:09,590
He doesn't need to ask, he just sees it and it's done.

451
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:12,760
Kent Loomis has the gift of service.

452
00:37:12,940 --> 00:37:14,460
He's never even heard me say that to his face.

453
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:15,420
There you are.

454
00:37:16,910 --> 00:37:17,410
But you do.

455
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:20,080
They don't know why.

456
00:37:20,180 --> 00:37:24,920
They just have a heart to see the background things done that the kingdom of God might grow.

457
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:26,360
And they don't want the recognition.

458
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,560
I'm always giving it to them, but they don't want it.

459
00:37:30,820 --> 00:37:33,580
But they just do what needs to be done.

460
00:37:34,160 --> 00:37:36,000
Because God has gifted them for that.

461
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:42,740
And when they're not serving like that, they're itchy and antsy because they're not using their spiritual gift.

462
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:48,670
Praise God for those with the gift of service in our midst, and more of you have it.

463
00:37:49,450 --> 00:37:51,910
I want to help you discover it and discern it.

464
00:37:53,820 --> 00:37:58,440
This last one under red gifts is the one that most people groan at.

465
00:38:00,410 --> 00:38:01,870
And you might do a collective groan here.

466
00:38:01,930 --> 00:38:02,430
Here we go.

467
00:38:02,790 --> 00:38:04,690
The gift of singleness.

468
00:38:10,780 --> 00:38:11,940
There are some people.

469
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:16,200
See, you groan because you don't have it.

470
00:38:17,940 --> 00:38:21,470
This doesn't sound good to you at all because you don't have the gift.

471
00:38:21,470 --> 00:38:28,010
The gift of singleness is for those who are gifted that they might do ministry more effectively

472
00:38:28,010 --> 00:38:31,190
as a single individual than as a married person.

473
00:38:32,460 --> 00:38:39,030
The reality is, when you're married and when you add kids to the picture, you are busy

474
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:43,510
and your interests are divided in a variety of areas.

475
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:51,030
But if you have the gift of singleness coupled with other gifts, usually in the area of church

476
00:38:51,030 --> 00:38:59,940
planting, cross-cultural missions, and the like. You are able to deal with all the craziness and

477
00:38:59,940 --> 00:39:11,170
the flexibility required to use those other gifts without the pressures of family. I've met a few of

478
00:39:11,170 --> 00:39:18,440
these people. I've heard about them. I've read about them as well. I read about a scholar who

479
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:25,500
is able to do deep work and focus in his work because God has gifted them, that man, in

480
00:39:25,500 --> 00:39:26,240
the area of singleness.

481
00:39:26,820 --> 00:39:27,580
He's not bitter.

482
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:30,340
He doesn't want those responsibilities.

483
00:39:30,340 --> 00:39:37,040
He is perfectly happy and fulfilled serving the Lord without the other distractions.

484
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:44,510
And for others, that sounds awful because you don't have the gift of singleness.

485
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:55,860
Let me just conclude by this.

486
00:39:59,220 --> 00:40:02,570
You might be overwhelmed, but that's okay.

487
00:40:03,900 --> 00:40:08,100
Because it's my hope that in the following weeks this will become clearer and clearer

488
00:40:08,100 --> 00:40:12,080
and that October 6th, you'll figure it out.

489
00:40:13,460 --> 00:40:14,340
Now when was that?

490
00:40:15,380 --> 00:40:16,500
October 6th.

491
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:17,760
You'll all be here.

492
00:40:19,270 --> 00:40:21,930
You can grow in your spiritual gifts.

493
00:40:22,750 --> 00:40:24,870
You may be gifted in an area.

494
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:30,940
But as you flex that muscle and work it and strengthen it,

495
00:40:30,940 --> 00:40:34,220
that gift will become even more effective.

496
00:40:36,060 --> 00:40:43,060
So just because you have a gift does not mean you don't have to practice and use it and experiment with it.

497
00:40:44,050 --> 00:40:47,170
You continually need to grow and work with it.

498
00:40:47,170 --> 00:40:54,490
And I would encourage you as you're discovering these gifts to seek opportunities that are consistent with using the gift

499
00:40:54,490 --> 00:40:59,910
and experiment and get in there and try and stretch it and work the gift.

500
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:06,360
And of course, you need to have a continued attitude in your life of godliness.

501
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:10,970
These are not for your self-aggrandizement.

502
00:41:11,850 --> 00:41:15,310
The gifts are not for you to call attention to yourself.

503
00:41:16,770 --> 00:41:23,640
Some of the gifts, when utilized, may put you in public arenas.

504
00:41:25,020 --> 00:41:29,200
And it takes a humble person to be able to realize that they are gifted by God

505
00:41:29,200 --> 00:41:33,200
and that they owe everything they're doing to God

506
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:37,350
and they must keep their character pure

507
00:41:37,350 --> 00:41:39,370
so that God can use them

508
00:41:39,370 --> 00:41:41,410
because it's not about them.

509
00:41:46,980 --> 00:41:50,580
I like this final quote from a man named Elmer Towns.

510
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:51,240
He said this.

511
00:41:51,340 --> 00:41:51,600
He said,

512
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:54,980
Do everything you can until you're 40,

513
00:41:55,520 --> 00:41:58,500
then settle down and do what you do best.

514
00:42:00,240 --> 00:42:01,640
That's good advice, isn't it?

515
00:42:03,220 --> 00:42:04,940
Do everything you can until you're 40

516
00:42:04,940 --> 00:42:08,040
and then settle down and do what you do best.

517
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:12,720
I think that applies to spiritual gifts.

518
00:42:15,250 --> 00:42:19,530
Because when you figure out what God has gifted you to do,

519
00:42:22,300 --> 00:42:24,840
you'll stop trying all the other stuff.

520
00:42:25,780 --> 00:42:27,000
You'll get focused.

521
00:42:28,210 --> 00:42:34,110
Because there you're discovering that that's where you fit in the body of Christ.

522
00:42:35,900 --> 00:42:37,640
We're all parts of a body.

523
00:42:38,460 --> 00:42:41,120
And as Paul illustrated, we're all connected together.

524
00:42:41,120 --> 00:42:45,560
And when some of you aren't using your gifts, the body is sick.

525
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:52,320
When we all begin to discover and use the gifts, the body grows healthy.

526
00:42:52,740 --> 00:42:58,400
You find joy because you realize that God is using you to be effective in the kingdom.

527
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:02,800
And what a privilege and high honor that is.

528
00:43:03,980 --> 00:43:07,360
So friends, discover what God has given you to do best.

529
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:12,840
and focus there and enjoy it for the glory of God's kingdom.

530
00:43:13,220 --> 00:43:15,880
Will you discover your spiritual gifts?

531
00:43:17,100 --> 00:43:21,060
Will you commit to be empowered and to use them

532
00:43:21,060 --> 00:43:24,820
and to be trained in them for God's glory

533
00:43:24,820 --> 00:43:26,820
and the growth of the kingdom?

534
00:43:28,340 --> 00:43:28,980
I hope so.

535
00:43:29,620 --> 00:43:30,120
Let's pray.

536
00:43:30,120 --> 00:43:35,580
Father, thank you for the encouragement of the realities

537
00:43:35,580 --> 00:43:41,850
of how you gift believers for service and for the kingdom.

538
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:46,820
And I pray that this congregation, over the next four weeks,

539
00:43:48,340 --> 00:43:52,070
would have a heightened awareness of where they're gifted,

540
00:43:53,380 --> 00:43:55,160
of how they plug into your kingdom,

541
00:43:55,700 --> 00:43:59,900
and what you have for them as a body of believers and individually.

542
00:44:00,380 --> 00:44:06,610
And I pray that these messages would be used by your spirit

543
00:44:06,610 --> 00:44:09,720
to get deep into our hearts and souls,

544
00:44:09,860 --> 00:44:12,840
and help us figure out where we belong

545
00:44:12,840 --> 00:44:16,640
and that in so doing we would see

546
00:44:16,640 --> 00:44:19,080
an increased sense of joy and service

547
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:22,210
and an increased effectiveness.

548
00:44:24,770 --> 00:44:26,950
So Father, use the next few weeks

549
00:44:26,950 --> 00:44:29,250
and this time of reflection on gifts

550
00:44:29,250 --> 00:44:31,430
to speak to your people.

551
00:44:33,490 --> 00:44:35,950
And then Father, I pray that we as a church body

552
00:44:35,950 --> 00:44:38,710
would be faithful to releasing these gifts

553
00:44:38,710 --> 00:44:40,790
to these people in this community

554
00:44:40,790 --> 00:44:43,310
that your kingdom may grow far and wide

555
00:44:43,310 --> 00:44:51,100
and that Fullerton First Baptist would be a place that the enemy would have to reckon with

556
00:44:51,100 --> 00:44:56,620
because we are your people doing what you've called us to do.

557
00:44:59,100 --> 00:45:00,940
So Lord, I look forward to seeing what you're going to do.

558
00:45:03,410 --> 00:45:09,220
Speak to us, teach us, and help us find our place.

559
00:45:12,230 --> 00:45:15,510
Now for a moment, I would like just to have your eyes continue to be closed

560
00:45:15,510 --> 00:45:16,870
and our heads bowed for a moment

561
00:45:16,870 --> 00:45:22,010
because I want to speak to all of us on a little different topic

562
00:45:22,010 --> 00:45:25,690
and it just relates to this,

563
00:45:25,790 --> 00:45:28,290
that you might be excited about these spiritual gifts,

564
00:45:28,370 --> 00:45:29,250
you might be intrigued,

565
00:45:29,390 --> 00:45:32,140
and you want to get on board with that,

566
00:45:34,080 --> 00:45:39,950
but you haven't yet decided that Jesus is the way,

567
00:45:40,950 --> 00:45:42,390
that he's the one to follow,

568
00:45:43,990 --> 00:45:45,830
that he's where real life is found.

569
00:45:47,810 --> 00:45:49,050
And you may have heard of him,

570
00:45:50,650 --> 00:45:52,150
but now you're sensing in your spirit

571
00:45:52,150 --> 00:45:53,990
it's time to give your life to him

572
00:45:53,990 --> 00:45:56,810
and then to have the Holy Spirit give you

573
00:45:56,810 --> 00:45:58,670
your gift or gifts.

574
00:45:59,150 --> 00:46:04,490
And if you're ready to find the Lord this morning

575
00:46:04,490 --> 00:46:08,820
and to leave knowing that he loves you and has forgiven you

576
00:46:08,820 --> 00:46:11,620
and that you'll be with the Lord forever,

577
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:13,640
that eternal life starts now,

578
00:46:13,700 --> 00:46:15,240
you might pray something like this.

579
00:46:16,680 --> 00:46:20,440
Dear God, I know that you're real

580
00:46:20,440 --> 00:46:24,080
and I now understand that you died for me,

581
00:46:25,030 --> 00:46:28,570
that through Jesus Christ you took away all of the wrongs I've done

582
00:46:28,570 --> 00:46:31,210
and that you allow me to start over

583
00:46:31,210 --> 00:46:32,730
and have a clean slate.

584
00:46:32,730 --> 00:46:37,200
and I look forward to following you

585
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:39,790
and discovering my spiritual gift

586
00:46:39,790 --> 00:46:41,150
that you're putting in me right now

587
00:46:41,150 --> 00:46:45,000
and that I might use it and follow you for your glory.

588
00:46:47,030 --> 00:46:49,900
So as far as I know how,

589
00:46:50,440 --> 00:46:51,620
I want to follow you every day.

590
00:46:52,860 --> 00:46:53,600
Teach me more

591
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:56,500
and thank you for your grace.

592
00:46:58,390 --> 00:47:00,550
In Jesus' name, amen.

